qa-hackathon-website
====================

DESCRIPTION

The QA Hackathon website available at http://qa-hackathon.org

This distribution contains all the HTML, CSS and images that are used within
the QA Hackathon website. Some content, particularly images, are the copyright 
of the respective authors, who have all allowed me to use these for the QA 
Hackathon website. If you wish to use them for other purposes, please contact 
myself and I will pass on your request to the respective copyright holders.

INSTALLATION

To install this distribution, simply unpack the distribution and copy the
./html directory into your web hosting directory structure. Using your 
favourite web server, edit the config files to use the ./html directory as the
document root.

CHANGES

For a complete list of changes, see the Changes file.

SUPPORT

If you find any typos or bugs, or wish to help extend or translate the website,
please clone a copy of the git repository [1] and submit a pull request for me
to review. 

Fixes are dependent upon their severity and my availability. Should a fix not
be forthcoming, please feel free to (politely) remind me.

[1] http://github.com/barbie/qa-hackathon-website

